{
  "texts": [
    "Keeping up with these changes demands ongoing investments in research, development, and monitoring, which can strain resources over time.Third, compliance and regulatory requirements in industries such as healthcare, smart cities, and defense are subject to stringent regulatory frameworks (e.g., HIPAA for healthcare, GDPR for data protection).",
    "Meeting these compliance standards often requires specific cybersecurity measures and audits.",
    "Compliance requirements can impose additional costs and administrative burdens on organizations, potentially making long-term sustainability challenging [26].Fourth, we address data volume and privacy concerns.",
    "Healthcare and smart city initiatives generate vast amounts of sensitive data.",
    "Protecting these data requires robust cybersecurity measures, including encryption, secure storage, and access controls."
  ]
}